Reasoning: The paper discusses the connection between information measures and estimation measures in the context of binomial and negative binomial models. This topic falls under the broad area of information theory and machine learning, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category as it directly deals with information measures. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely as they cover topics related to estimation and modeling. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.ST (Statistics Theory) are less likely but still possible as they cover topics related to statistical modeling and inference.
